<title>UK: EMI ends merger talks with Seagram - paper.</title>
<headline>EMI ends merger talks with Seagram - paper.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-04-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Recording company EMI Group may have broken off merger talks with Seagram the Canadian drinks and entertainment group after failing to reach an agreement, according to the Financial Times.</p>
<p>Bid speculation for EMI had intensified last summer when the group demerged from its former parent Thorn EMI which split its music and rental businesses.</p>
<p>Seagram -- with its Universal Music subsidiary -- had been viewed as the likeliest bidder for EMI and talks between the two companies may have begun before Christmas, but analysts believe Seagram may still put in a bid, the article said.</p>
<p>Other possible bidders for EMI include Walt Disney, News Corporation and Viacom as well as U.S. computer software group Microsoft, said the Financial Times.</p>
<p>But there is also a possibility that an investor outside the entertainments industry might be attracted to EMI, it added.</p>
